article.headline: Utah State 73, New Mexico State 57
article.story: LOGAN, Utah (AP) -- Behind the 20-point shooting of 6-foot-9 center Mike Ahmad, Utah State won its 10th straight Gossner Foods Holiday Classic Tournament Tuesday night, beating New Mexico State 73-57. Utah State (8-1) held a comfortable lead throughout the game and outrebounded New Mexico State (6-5) by a 29-15 margin. Spencer Nelson, who was named Gossner Classic MVP, also notched a double-double with 11 points and 10 assists for USU. Nate Harris added 10 points for USU. In a battle that pitted Aggies against Aggies, Utah State maintained its perfect record in the Gossner tournament. New Mexico State was led by Duane John with 15 points, and James Moore added 14. Utah State took a comfortable 40-27 lead into the lockerroom as its offense connected on 13-of-23 from the field and 12-of-16 from the free-throw line. It finished the night shooting 25-of-51 from the field and 20-of-25 from the free-throw line. Earlier Tuesday night, San Francisco won consolation honors with a 70-69 victory over Texas-San Antonio.
